# Code-signing material — never committed. CI injects the .pfx from a secret;
# the public .cer is derived from the key by build_driver_msi.ps1 at build time.
OpenMotion_signing_cert.pfx
OpenMotion_signing_cert.cer

# Build outputs produced by build_driver_msi.ps1 / CI (the signing key is the
# single source of truth). The distributable zip is vendored in bloodflow-app.
# NOTE: all four .cat files ARE committed content -- the 3 sensor cats are proven
# libwdi/inf2cat content, and openmotion-dfu.cat is regenerated only on INF
# change (build_driver_msi.ps1 -RegenCats). The build re-signs catalogs only
# when the signing key changes.
OpenMotionDriver-x64.zip
OpenMotionDriver-x64.msi
cab1.cab
*.wixpdb
